info.name: PHDapi-Regression
info.description:
# Introduction
Collection for PHDapi 
# Overview

Things that the developers should know about

PHDapi test collection. this collection follows QO V2 statging collection folder. 
Folder is further divided into use cases. These use cases cover a specific flow using PHDAPI
API's are chained in order to create a flow.
Each folder has description of the use case and are tagged with numeric id.

# Authentication
What is the preferred way of using the API?
Authenticate your service and then login the user to perform actions on the web. Each call requires a
authorization: access_token= this comes from qosigner tool which generates a google auth token.
auth_token is generated once user signs in.


# Error Codes
What errors and status codes can a user expect?

	| STATUS CODE | STATUS CODE DESCRIPTION                                                                                                                       |
	|-------------|--------------------------------------------|
	| 200         | Successful response. For Example                                                                                                              |
	|             | Cart is created for a guest or authenticated customer. A cart ID is returned.                                                                 |
	| 400         | Missing required parameters or invalid data.                                                                                                  |
	| 401         | Invalid token.                                                                                                                                |
	| 404         | Failed to initialize cart.                                                                                                                    |
	| 406         | Not Acceptable.                                                                                                                               |
	| 409         | Invalid delivery address.                                                                                                                     |
	| 444         | Unknown or invalid response received from backend service.                                                                                    |
	| 422         | Another error occurred/ Unprocessable Entity                                                                                                  |
	| 201         | Successful response. Favorite order is added to the cart, but without the unavailable products or modifiers. Cart and conflicts are returned. |
	| 410         | Unable to validate order.                                                                                                                     |
	| default     | Error payload                                                                                                                                 |
	| 204         | Successful response. Address is deleted.                                           	                                                           |
	| 403         | Unauthorized. User must call POST /customer/privileged first.                                                                                 |
	| 304         | Not modified. No changes to nutrition data.                                                                                                   |



# Rate limit
Is there a limit to the number of requests an user can send? bench marking has not been defined.
None tested at this time.

item.description:
Runs the test to Get Customer loyality from T3
uses QO calls to get the Customer ID and then calls T3 with customer ID returned from QO
*** NOTE: requires Google Auth token.

Test Case & Scope : get loyality point for a valid customer.
	Steps: 
		Authenticate the API.
		Clear any existing customer tokens.
		Login a customer with valid accounts and credentials.
		Perform get Customer call to get ccustomer id. Pass this id to next call.
		Using customer id from previous step, call get customer loyality.
		Revoke token to ready test script for next test.
	Scope: This test case covers. Only Authenticated customer can retrieve loyality account details.

Response Codes Scope: test scripts covers
		200: Valid, successfull response is retuned with Loyality points of authenticated account.
		404: No loyality points exist for the account queried.
		500: unable to connect to backend due to server being down.

No State is provided, Only zip Code

while testing from postman, you can provide zip as 2,4,
and digit upto 5 and it will retrieve stores. there is no
validation on postal_code field of the payload.

request.description:
Returns a list of stores supporting the chosen occassion, ordered by closest to farthest relative to the request point.
* for Delivery you will need to provide an address for it to send back a valid response.

API response bring back list of store in the given zipcode.
while testing from postman, you can provide zip as 2,4,
and digit upto 5 and it will retrieve stores. there is no
validation on postal_code field of the payload.

request.description:
Returns a list of stores supporting the chosen occassion, ordered by closest to farthest relative to the request point.
* for Delivery you will need to provide an address for it to send back a valid response.

API response bring back list of store in the given zipcode.
while testing from postman, you can provide zip as 2,4,
and digit upto 5 and it will retrieve stores. there is no
validation on postal_code field of the payload.

{

"city": "Plano",
"state": "TX",
"postal_code": 75024,
"country": "",
"latitude": "",
"longitude": "",
"limit": 5,
"occasion_id": "CARRYOUT"
}-->

request.description:
Returns a list of stores supporting the chosen occassion, ordered by closest to farthest relative to the request point.
* for Delivery you will need to provide an address for it to send back a valid response.

API response bring back list of store in the given zipcode.
while testing from postman, you can provide zip as 2,4,
and digit upto 5 and it will retrieve stores. there is no
validation on postal_code field of the payload.

"longitude": "",
"limit": 5,
"occasion_id": "CARRYOUT"
}-->

request.description:
Returns a list of stores supporting the chosen occassion, ordered by closest to farthest relative to the request point.
* for Delivery you will need to provide an address for it to send back a valid response.

API response bring back list of store in the given zipcode.
while testing from postman, you can provide zip as 2,4,
and digit upto 5 and it will retrieve stores. there is no
validation on postal_code field of the payload.

request.description:
Returns a list of stores supporting the chosen occassion, ordered by closest to farthest relative to the request point.
* for Delivery you will need to provide an address for it to send back a valid response.

API response bring back list of store in the given zipcode.
while testing from postman, you can provide zip as 2,4,
and digit upto 5 and it will retrieve stores. there is no
validation on postal_code field of the payload.

request.description:
Returns a list of stores supporting the chosen occassion, ordered by closest to farthest relative to the request point.
* for Delivery you will need to provide an address for it to send back a valid response.

API response bring back list of store in the given zipcode.
while testing from postman, you can provide zip as 2,4,
and digit upto 5 and it will retrieve stores. there is no
validation on postal_code field of the payload.

GIVEN a customer is placing an order for the delivery occasion
AND there are products requiring age verification in the cart

AC2
GIVEN a customer is placing an order for the delivery occasion
AND there are products requiring age verification in the cart
AND the payment method is CREDIT
AND the user has verified their age
WHEN POST on /orders is run
THEN the order should be submitted successfully

AC3

AND the user has verified their age
WHEN POST on /orders is run
THEN the order should be submitted successfully
 
AC4
GIVEN a customer is placing an order for the carryout occasion
AND there are products requiring age verification in the cart
AND the payment method is cash, credit or gift card

item.description:
Runs the test to Get Customer loyality from T3
uses QO calls to get the Customer ID and then calls T3 with customer ID returned from QO
*** NOTE: requires Google Auth token.

This set of API will cover User stories for Loyalty enhacements
Loyalty Endpoints 

PHDAPI: added 2 endpoints to provide functionality of locking and unlocking points at T3 for Native APP.
 
List of endpoints
Lock Points 	[ POST ]/customer/coupon?key=key	PHDAPI
Unlock Points 	[ DELETE ] /customer/coupon?key=key	PHDAPI
Remove Discount	 	 
 
To Initiate lock endpoint, App will need to call get customer loyalty on authenticated customer. In order to get the following values
"	Available rewards on the account.
"	Available loyalty point
"	How many points are already locked.
"	How many are pending
"	If the coupons are present in the customer loyalty account: this is the array where you will have a coupon
"	In order to lock points you will use "KEY" value within rewards array of response received from Get Customer loyalty.
 
Lock points Endpoints when called with  "key" in request payload. Returns the associated key and loyalty rewards that's available for that key . Get Customer loyalty end point should be called again to verify that points are now locked
Once locked points are verified. User the "Associated_key" returned from lock points response. Pass the value to Add discount request. For Example: if the loyalty reward calls for free large pizza, add the pizza product and the "associated_key" in the request payload. Returned response should be successful with cart loaded with added discount and product. You should be able to see the mapped loyalty code with associated key in response. Below is what that [ key-->associated_key-->coupon code ] Mapping results in.
Coupon Code	Key
GHLOYALTY	2
GRLOYALTY	1
T90LOYALTY	27
PFXI	31
FLASH_50	40
KMA_8_30	39
 
                   Response from Lock Points 
{
"created_coupon":
        {
        "code":"GRLOYALTY",
        "points":250,
        "coupon_association_key":1795,
        "type":"redemption",
        "coupon_key":1,
        "gifted":false,
        "name":"Large Any Pizza"
        },
"locked_points":250,
"coupon_data"
[
        {
        "code":"GRLOYALTY",
        "points":250,
        "coupon_association_key":1795,
        "type":"redemption",
        "coupon_key":1,
        "gifted":false,
        "name":"Large Any Pizza"}
],
"qo_id":"17030603132457270672167772",
"available_points":2610.0
}
Once the order is placed successfully. Calling Get customer loyalty end point will give you the points on the account.
Along with last order placed using loyalty rewards, Points used for that order. New account total points will reflect the new number of points after subtracting the points used in last order.  
 
Unlock Points:
Pre conditions:
"	Points should be locked in order to unlock
"	Associated_key must be passed in order to unlock points
"	( app should retain this key till order is placed or removed from cart).
"	Points in redeemed status can not be unlocked.
"	Once the Order is placed.  You have to call the store to in order to unlock points.
"	Lock points only unlock after QO updated the T3 with order status on each order. This is 24
"	Hour wait for unlocking cancelled or abandoned orders in cart.
Once the points are locked, app can call unlock endpoint using "associated_key". This will make available locked points in customer account. Customer account can be verified by calling " GET customer Loyalty".
QO Update related to Loyalty:
 user can now call Remove Discount along with flag "keep_products=true" as query params. This will result in only removing the discount from the cart and unlock the points associated to the cart.(If the cart has loyalty points).
Points are unlocked can be verified by called "Get Loyalty" and products can be verified in response of Remove Discounts ( when flag is set to true ).
If Remove discount is called with  "keep_products=false" , then entire cart is cleared of products and discount.
Points are unlocked by QO automatically, This can be verified by calling "Get loyalty" end point.
"	Case when only discount is removed: Cart returned must have price associated to the order.
